data.body:
Fixes #20855 

---

@bpasero not having this could potentially cause an obscure bug if the debug commands were ever registered before the workbench stuff. Feel free to close this off if it was done intentionally.

- VSCode Version: 1.9.1
- OS Version: macOS 10.12.1

Steps to Reproduce:
Create 3 files in the same folder:

Schema.json:
```javascript
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
  "properties": {
    "format": {
      "oneOf": [
        {
          "type": "string",
          "enum": [
            "value1",
            "value2"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "string",
          "format": "uri"
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

Example.json
```javascript
{
    "$schema": "./Schema.json",
    "format": "value1"
}
```
Actual: 'Warning' message: 'Matches multiple schemas when only one must validate.'
Expected: No warnings

Example2.json
```javascript
{
    "$schema": "./Schema.json",
    "format": "file://test"
}
```
Actual: No warnings

Note: There are no warnings with those examples when validating using http://www.jsonschemavalidator.net
